<h1 style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 20pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 20pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2 Overview of Project</span></h1>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">This section will provide a general overview of the project and its background.</span></p>
<h2 style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2.1 Background</span></h2>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The first inspiration behind &ldquo;NuFu&rdquo; came after the constant hike in prices from streaming services. Most notably Netflix recently raised their prices to a whopping $12/month for the cheapest HD plan. This caused an uproar amongst many casual customers who have netflix just to watch a few select shows and movies. Although the $12 price tag might be worth it for what Netflix is offering in return, many users have and most likely will not take full advantage to justify the increase in price. </span></p>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Secondly, many homes now have both Netflix and Hulu accounts to make sure they can watch shows from both platforms. However, that also means the user has to pay a premium $12/month for Netflix and an additional $10/month for Hulu. That is over $22/month just to watch a handful of shows for most people. This doesn&rsquo;t include the additional $100+ most families pay for cable and the like. It has come to a point to where most teenagers and young adults have decided to either unsubscribe from these services completely or share an account with a friend to split the pricey costs. Netflix and other services have responded to account sharing between non-family members by enforcing a limit to how many people can watch simultaneously. However, this did not push the people account sharing to subscribe with their own account, rather it just made them stop using the service completely. All in all, people are paying for too much content, 99% of which they will never use nor do they have the time to make use of them. </span></p>
<h1 style="line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 20pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;">&nbsp;</h1>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Finally, Disney announced last year that they will be coming out with their own streaming service. Following this announcement, they asked Netflix to discontinue shows that Disney has the licence to, most notably the Marvel show series. Most likely, Disney will continue those shows on their own service when it comes out in the near future but questions regarding who will play the characters the audience have grown to love and where will the show pick up from have had some customers outraged. This will just lead to another competing streaming service that most customers will likely have to subscribe to since Disney has the rights to a lot shows and movies. </span></p>
