</ul>
<h2 style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2.3 Contextual Information</span></h2>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">This service is modeled after similar streaming and video viewing sites. The primary site that this service is influenced from is Netflix with its subscription service and media viewing cite. Our project also gathers influence from websites like Youtube and various movie rating sites. Like Youtube, our service will allow users to rate videos, but instead of rating on the basis of "thumbs up" or "thumbs down," each user is allowed to rate on a scale of one star to five stars, with the comments being used to explain their reasoning. </span></p>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">In contrast to Netflix, our service gives the user ten "slots," from which they pick certain series that they want to watch. Unlike sites like Amazon or Netflix, where the user has to pay the full subscription price even if they only use a small fraction of the services, our site is more affordable and allows the user to pick the shows that they actually want to see. This allows the user to pick and choose what they want to watch without wasting money on paying for services that they won't even use. The user is also able to buy a new slot for a new show for the month if they want to watch another one.</span></p>
